{
  "text": ", while those that vanish against q MN can be safely absorbed into transformations of W αβ MN . The sole subtlety here is that one must take the Lagrange multiplier, λ, to transform under generalised diffeomorphisms and external diffeomorphisms in order to cancel the extra weight terms, similarly to the particle case [CITATION_1] .",
  "correct_citation": {
